                <p dir=3D"ltr"><span>Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) is =
a factorization method in linear algebra that decomposes a matrix into thre=
e other matrices, providing a way to represent data in terms of its singula=
r values.</span></p><p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"text-align: left;"><span> SVD h=
elps you split that table into three parts:</span></p><ul><li value=3D"1"><=
b><strong>U</strong></b><span>: This part tells you about the people (like =
their general preferences).</span></li><li value=3D"2"><b><strong>=CE=A3</s=
trong></b><span>: This part shows how important each factor is (how much ea=
ch rating matters).</span></li><li value=3D"3"><b><strong>V=E1=B5=80</stron=
g></b><span>: This part tells you about the products (how similar they are =
to each other)</span></li></ul><p dir=3D"ltr"><span>Lets understand this wi=
th help of an example: Suppose you have a small table of people=E2=80=99s r=
atings for two movies,</span></p><table><thead><tr><th><p dir=3D"ltr"><span=
